        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>+ In nomine domini salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi Dei aeterni. <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/157">Paldolfus</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/167">Landolfus</persName> divina ordinante
                        providentia Longobardorum gentis <rs key="#Princeps">principes</rs>. Cum
                        principalis excellentia dilectis sui petitione petentis clementer favet.
                        Igitur noverit omnium <rs key="#fidelisOf #Assembly">fidelium nostrorum
                            presentium</rs> scilicet ac futurorum solertia quai <persName
                            ref="#people/2428" key="#Intercessory">Burrellum</persName> […]
                            <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Riverbed #Mountains #Villas #Casalia #Landed_possessions #Forests #Gualdi #Wine #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Agricultural_workers #Fountains #Churches #Freeborn"
                            ref="#places/2843">Petra Abundantis</placeName> fidelis noster una cum
                        uxore sua <persName ref="#people/2429" key="#Intercessory">Ruta</persName>
                        et cum filiis suis scilicet <persName ref="#people/2430" key="#Intercessory"
                            >Iohanne Burrello</persName> et <persName ref="#people/2431"
                            key="#Intercessory">Oderisio</persName>, obsecravit nostram excelletiam,
                        ut pro amore omnipotentis Dei et salvatione animae nostae concederemus in
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Churches #Landed_possessions
                            #Mountains #Forests #Gualdi #Rivers #Riverbed #Fountains #Wine #Casalia 
                            #Villas #Agricultural_workers #Freeborn"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/84">Beati Benedicti confessoris
                            Christi</orgName> situs in <rs key="#Mountains">monte</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Mountains #Monasteries #Abbots" ref="#places/109"
                            >Casino</placeName>, ubi nunc Deo auxiliante domno <persName
                            key="#Abbots" ref="#people/309">Aligerno</persName> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> praesse videtur ad possessionem prephati
                        monasterii et de eius abbatibus et rectoribus in perpetuum <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Landed_possessions #Mountains #Forests #Gualdi #Rivers #Riverbed #Fountains #Wine #Casalia #Villas #Agricultural_workers #Freeborn
                            #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2316">Sancti Eustasii</orgName> de Arcu in <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Churches #Landed_possessions #Mountains #Forests #Gualdi #Rivers #Riverbed #Fountains #Wine #Casalia #Villas #Agricultural_workers #Freeborn #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1943">Molisie</geogName> situm prope <rs>castrum</rs>
                        Petra Habundantis , quam obtulerunt ipsi beato Benedicto de monte Casino,
                        cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, montibus, planis, <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis</rs>, <rs key="#Riverbed">aquarumque decursibus</rs>, qualiter
                        inferius declaramus; de quibus petiit a nostra excellentia ut firmitatis
                        apices in eodem sancto monasterio fieri iuberemus, cuius petitionem
                        exaudientes hos firmitatis apices ibidem exide fieri iussimus. Per quos
                        omnino sancimus et perpetualiter habedum nostris et futuris temporibus
                        concedimus in eodem sancto loco ecclesiam Sancti Eustasii supradictam, cum
                        omnibus suis possessionibus, quomodo incipit da ipsa <rs key="#Fountains"
                            >fonte</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Fountains">Coperclata</placeName>, et ascendit per viam
                        baldensem ad petre posite iusta fontem <placeName key="#Fountains"
                            >Gualderii</placeName>, et inde descendit per ballonem de <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions">Macclaroteca</placeName>, ad rivum <placeName
                            key="#Rivers">Falascosum</placeName>, et inde ascendit in <rs
                            key="#Roads">biam</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Roads" ref="#places/2316">Isernia</placeName>, et
                        rebolvente vadit per ipsam biam ad fontem de <placeName key="#Fountains"
                            >Turricella</placeName> et in rivum vivum, et per ipsum rivum descendit
                        in <rs key="#Gualdi">vadum</rs> de <placeName key="#Gualdi"
                            >Castanea</placeName>, et ascendit per rivum unde verni temporis aqua
                        decurrit, usque in rivum siccum et inde descendit in fluvio <placeName
                            key="#Rivers">Berrino</placeName>, et per ipsum flumen ascendit in rivum
                        vivum, et per ipsum rivum vivum ascendit in rivum <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            >Francoli</placeName>, et per ipsum rivum Francoli in iunturam vallonis
                        devenit a femonis, et ascendit in rivum <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            >Rubeum</placeName> et per ipsum rivum Rubeum in via que vadit ad dictum
                        casrum Petra Abunnantis a fonte Coperdato, et per ipsam viam redit ad primum
                        finem. Ea videlicet ratione quod supradicta ecclesia Sancti Eustasii cum
                        supradictis possessionibus in prephato sancto monasterio beati Benedicti
                        concedimus, et confirmamus abendi ac possidendi cum viis et aquis et cum
                        omnibus suis pertinentiis inferius et superius in perpetuum. Et si
                        infradictis possessionibus <rs key="#Agricultural_workers #Freeborn"
                            >homines</rs> habitaverint et fuerint ibi <rs key="#Villas">villas</rs>
                        seu <rs key="#Casalia">casalia</rs>, ipsi homines semper sint sub dicione
                        beati Benedicti, et nullus homo aliud eis precipiat aut aliquid tollat de
                        bonis eorum, nisi per abbatem dicti monasterii, quod si magna vel altra
                        persona contra hoc venire presumserit nostro palatio libras auri centum
                        componat, et hoc praesens privilegium in sua firmitate semper permaneat, ut
                        autem haec nostra concessio verius credatur, manu propria scripsimus, et ex
                        anulo nostro subpter fecimus sigillari. (M) Signum domni Paldolfi
                        excellentissimi principis <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> ex iussione supradicta potestatis me
                        subscripsi. Datum duodecima martii anno tricesimo quarto principatus domni
                        Paldolfi, et anno vicesimo sebtimo principatus domni Landolfi gloriosis
                        principibus indictione quinta. Actum in <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities #fidelisOf #Assembly" ref="#places/173"
                            >Capuana</placeName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
